# SmartQueue — Production Feature Roadmap

All features map to real files in the codebase. Ordered by impact and dependency.

---

## Phase 1 — Core Usability Fixes & Quick Wins (Week 1)

### 🐛 Bug Fix — Reception [updateStatus](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/reception/page.tsx#128-137) calls wrong endpoints
[reception/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/reception/page.tsx) calls `PUT /queue/update/:id` but backend only has `/complete/:id` and `/cancel/:id`.
#### [MODIFY] [reception/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/reception/page.tsx)
- `COMPLETED` → `api.put('/queue/complete/${id}')`
- `CANCELLED` → `api.put('/queue/cancel/${id}')`

---

### Feature 1A — Patient Notes Field
Receptionist adds a brief clinical note when registering ("chest pain", "follow-up BP"). Doctor sees it before calling.
#### [MODIFY] [Patient.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/models/Patient.js) — add `notes: { type: String, default: "" }`
#### [MODIFY] [pat_validator.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/validators/pat_validator.js) — add optional `notes` field
#### [MODIFY] [queueRoutes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/queueRoutes.js) — pass `notes` to `Patient.create()`
#### [MODIFY] [reception/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/reception/page.tsx) — add `notes` textarea in Add Patient form

---

### Feature 1B — Pause with Message
Doctor types a reason when pausing ("Emergency — back in 20 mins"). Patients see it on the live tracking page.
#### [MODIFY] [User.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/models/User.js) — add `pauseMessage: { type: String, default: "" }`
#### [MODIFY] [doctorRoutes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/doctorRoutes.js) — save `pauseMessage` in `PUT /availability`
#### [MODIFY] [doctor/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/doctor/page.tsx) — show message input on "Paused" select
#### [MODIFY] [queueRoutes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/queueRoutes.js) — return `pauseMessage` in `GET /status/:id`
#### [MODIFY] status tracking page — display message when doctor is paused

---

### Feature 1C — Multi-Doctor Simultaneous View (Receptionist)
A single grid showing all assigned doctors' queues side-by-side instead of sequential iteration.
#### [MODIFY] [reception/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/reception/page.tsx)
- Replace flat queue array with a `Map<doctorId, patients[]>` structure
- Render a column per doctor in a responsive grid layout
- Each column has its own "Mark Complete" / "Cancel" buttons

---

## Phase 2 — Doctor Productivity (Week 2)

### Feature 2A — Priority Flag from Doctor Side
Doctor can pull any patient to position #1 with one tap (elderly, emergency walkup).
#### [MODIFY] [queueRoutes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/queueRoutes.js)
- Add `PUT /queue/prioritise/:patientId` — sets `tokenNumber = 0` and shifts all others up
#### [MODIFY] [doctor/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/doctor/page.tsx)
- Add a live queue list view to the doctor dashboard
- Each row has a "🔺 Prioritise" button

---

### Feature 2B — Doctor Daily Summary
"Today at a Glance" card: patients seen, avg consultation time today, busiest hour, no-show count.
#### [MODIFY] [queueRoutes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/queueRoutes.js)
- Add `GET /queue/summary/today` (DOCTOR auth)
- Aggregate from [Patient](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/reception/page.tsx#107-127): count completed/cancelled today, time delta stats, peak hour bucket
#### [MODIFY] [doctor/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/doctor/page.tsx)
- Fetch on load, render 4-stat card row below settings area

---

### Feature 2C — Drag & Drop Queue Reorder (Receptionist)
Drag tokens to reorder the queue visually. Backend already supports `PUT /queue/reorder/:doctorId`.
#### [MODIFY] [reception/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/reception/page.tsx)
- Install `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable`
- Replace the static table rows with sortable drag items
- On drop, call `api.put('/queue/reorder/:doctorId', { newOrder })` which already exists

---

## Phase 3 — Patient Engagement & Notifications (Week 3)

### Feature 3A — WhatsApp / SMS Notifications
On registration: "You're #3 in Dr. Sharma's queue. Track live: [link]". At position #2: "You're almost up — please come in."

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Requires MSG91 (India, ~₹0.15/SMS or ₹1.20/WhatsApp) or Twilio. Free sandbox available for testing.

#### [NEW] [utils/notificationService.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/utils/notificationService.js)
- `sendQueueConfirmation(phone, name, position, trackingUrl, doctorName)`
- `sendNearlyUpAlert(phone, name, doctorName)`
#### [MODIFY] [queueRoutes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/queueRoutes.js)
- Call `sendQueueConfirmation()` after `Patient.create()` in `POST /add`
- After `PUT /complete/:id`, check if next patient is now at position 2 → call `sendNearlyUpAlert()`
#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/.env) — add `MSG91_AUTH_KEY`, `MSG91_TEMPLATE_ID`

---

### Feature 3B — Feedback Collection (1–5 stars)
On visit completion, the patient's tracking page shows a 5-star rating. Collected passively.
#### [MODIFY] [Patient.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/models/Patient.js) — add `feedback: { rating: Number, comment: String }`
#### [NEW] `PUT /queue/feedback/:uniqueLinkId` in queueRoutes.js — public, no auth, saves `{ rating, comment }`
#### [MODIFY] status tracking page — show star rating UI when `status === "completed"`
#### [MODIFY] [admin/dashboard/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/admin/dashboard/page.tsx) — show avg rating per doctor in stats

---

### Feature 3C — QR Code Self-Registration
Patient scans QR at clinic → public page shows available doctors, queue sizes, ETAs → can self-register.
#### [NEW] [kiosk/[hospitalId]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/kiosk/%5BhospitalId%5D/page.tsx)
- Public page (no auth required)
- Fetches doctors via existing `GET /api/kiosk/:hospitalId/doctors`
- Form: name, phone, select doctor → `POST /queue/add` (needs a public token path — add `hospitalPublicKey` auth option)
#### [MODIFY] [admin/dashboard/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/admin/dashboard/page.tsx)
- Add "Clinic QR Code" section using `qrcode.react` pointing to `/kiosk/${hospitalId}`
- Include print/download button

---

## Phase 4 — Admin Power Features (Week 4)

### Feature 4A — Analytics Dashboard
Peak hours heatmap, wait time trend, completion rate, no-show rate per doctor.
#### [NEW] [admin/analytics/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/admin/analytics/page.tsx)
- Install `recharts`
- Line chart: patients/day last 30 days
- Bar chart: patients completed by doctor
- Heatmap table: hour × day of week patient volume
#### [MODIFY] [adminRoutes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/adminRoutes.js)
- Add `GET /admin/analytics?range=7d|30d` returning aggregated Patient data for the hospital

---

### Feature 4B — Staff Scheduling (Working Hours)
Admin sets each doctor's working hours. System auto-marks unavailable outside schedule.
#### [MODIFY] [User.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/models/User.js)
- Add `schedule: [{ day: String, startTime: String, endTime: String }]` to doctor fields
#### [MODIFY] [adminRoutes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/adminRoutes.js)
- Add `PUT /admin/staff/:id/schedule` endpoint
#### [NEW] Cron job (node-cron) — every 15 minutes, check all doctors' schedules and update `availability` automatically
#### [MODIFY] [admin/dashboard/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/%28dashboard%29/admin/dashboard/page.tsx)
- Add schedule editing UI per doctor (time range picker per day)

---

## Phase 5 — Infrastructure & Growth (Week 5+)

### Feature 5A — Kiosk Display Mode
Full-screen TV view showing current token + next 3 in queue. No interaction needed.
#### [NEW] [kiosk/[hospitalId]/display/page.tsx](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/frontend-next/src/app/kiosk/%5BhospitalId%5D/display/page.tsx)
- Existing `GET /api/kiosk/:hospitalId/display` backend route already exists
- Build a clean, large-font display page with auto-refresh every 10 seconds
- Show: "Now Serving: Token #7 — Dr. Sharma" and next 3 tokens

---

### Feature 5B — Multi-Branch Support
Clinic chains with multiple locations under one admin account.
#### [MODIFY] [Hospital.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/models/Hospital.js) — add `branches: [{ name, address, branchId }]`
#### [MODIFY] Auth JWT payload — include `branchId`
#### [MODIFY] All queue queries — add `branchId` filter alongside `hospitalId`

---

### Feature 5C — Prescription / Return Visit Reminder
Patient gets a WhatsApp reminder N days before their expected return, set by the doctor at end of visit.
#### [MODIFY] [Patient.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/models/Patient.js) — add `nextVisitDate: Date`
#### [MODIFY] complete endpoint — accept `nextVisitDate` from doctor
#### [NEW] Cron job — daily, find patients where `nextVisitDate = today + 1`, send WhatsApp via `notificationService`

---

### Feature 5D — Appointment Booking Layer
Walk-in queue + booked appointments in one unified system.
#### [NEW] `Appointment` model — `{ hospitalId, doctorId, patientName, phone, scheduledAt, tokenNumber, status }`
#### [NEW] Appointment routes — `POST /appointments/book`, `GET /appointments/doctor/:id/today`
#### [MODIFY] Queue system — merge walk-ins and appointments into a single ordered list per doctor session

---

### Feature 5E — HMS Integration API
Let hospitals plug SmartQueue into their existing Hospital Management System.
#### [MODIFY] [apiV1Routes.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/routes/apiV1Routes.js) — expand existing B2B API with:
- `POST /v1/queue/add` — add patient via API key (already partially built)
- `GET /v1/queue/status/:token` — query by token number
- `POST /v1/appointments/book`
- Webhook support for queue events (already have [Webhook.js](file:///c:/Smart-Queue/backend/models/Webhook.js) model)

---

## Implementation Order Summary

| Week | Focus | Features |
|------|-------|---------|
| 1 | Core fixes + quick wins | Bug fix, Patient Notes, Pause Message, Multi-doctor view |
| 2 | Doctor productivity | Priority flag, Daily summary, Drag & drop reorder |
| 3 | Patient engagement | SMS/WhatsApp, Feedback stars, QR self-registration |
| 4 | Admin control | Analytics dashboard, Staff scheduling |
| 5+ | Growth infrastructure | Kiosk display, Multi-branch, Reminders, Appointments, HMS API |
